name: Lt. Gov. Adam Gregg

name: Lt. Gov. Adam Gregg
tweet: Last night the Gregg family volunteered to package meals at Meals from the Heartland (@MftH). It was great to spend family time together fighting hunger!  #FeedingIowans #BeAHungerFighter  https://t.co/D25PaBRlwU

name: Lt. Gov. Adam Gregg
tweet: I spent this afternoon donating blood at @LifeServeBldCtr with my wife. Many blood centers are struggling to keep up with demand due to the pandemic. If you are able this holiday season, please consider the gift of donating blood. It saves lives!  https://t.co/Ycu1wS6BO8

name: Lt. Gov. Adam Gregg
tweet: I had the honor of speaking tonight at the @JoppaOutreach 2020 Iowa Homeless Memorial. It was a humbling reminder of the pain and suffering that homeless Iowans face.   Find information for volunteering / donating at Joppa here:   https://t.co/Mgmj60z3xp  #HPMD2020  https://t.co/8gkVdsc88m

name: Lt. Gov. Adam Gregg
tweet: ICYMI: Last week, Governor Reynolds received the latest @EmpowerRuralIA recommendations. These suggestions are aimed at improving coordination and aligning processes to spark innovation and fuel growth in rural Iowa.  Read all about them here:  https://t.co/iiHrzvJ29j

name: Lt. Gov. Adam Gregg
tweet: I had the chance to speak on the Enhancing Public Safety and Expanding Second Chances in Iowa panel from @RightOnCrime, @REFORM, and @FaithandFreedom.   Iowa is a national leader in criminal justice reform thanks to the work of the FOCUS Committee and support from @IAGovernor.  https://t.co/rRSdYa6TGq

name: Lt. Gov. Adam Gregg
tweet: Mississippi Valley Blood Center (@WillYouGive) is still in critical need of convalescent plasma donations. If you’ve recovered from COVID-19 and are able to donate, please consider scheduling an appointment at the link below.  #DonatePlasma    https://t.co/kKQhQgV5u0

name: Lt. Gov. Adam Gregg
tweet: A historic day for our state and country!  While news of a vaccine arriving in Iowa is great, we must continue to follow proper safety precautions until it can be widely distributed.

name: Lt. Gov. Adam Gregg
tweet: .@FOODBANKIOWA is a tremendous partner for the #FeedingIowans Task Force, and their CEO Michelle Book is an absolute champion in fighting food insecurity.  I’m glad Michelle could join me on some food pantry tours across the state.   https://t.co/YYTqYBrgfH

name: Lt. Gov. Adam Gregg
tweet: With the holiday season approaching, I encourage you to shop at Shop Iowa! You can get gifts for everyone on your list from local businesses across the state. All from the comfort of your home! #shopsmall

name: Lt. Gov. Adam Gregg
tweet: I’ve finished my #99CountyTour for 2020! This year brought unprecedented challenges, but I’m proud of the creative work we’ve done to serve Iowans in need.  For my final 13 stops this year I chose to highlight the great work local food pantries do to stop hunger.  #FeedingIowans  https://t.co/aIFta6KweG

name: Lt. Gov. Adam Gregg
tweet: I’m making stops at food pantries today on my #99CountyTour. It’s great to hear how the efforts of the #FeedingIowans Task Force have helped these pantries, and learn how we can better support their fight against food insecurity.  https://t.co/NmcL2W3hvc

name: Lt. Gov. Adam Gregg
tweet: Today, we remember the lives lost in Pearl Harbor 79 years ago. Their legacy of bravery and service continues to inspire our nation.

name: Lt. Gov. Adam Gregg
tweet: I made #99CountyTour stops at food pantries in Taylor, Page, Fremont, Montgomery, Adams, and Adair counties today.  These pantries play a critical role in stopping hunger, and I encourage everyone to support their efforts this Holiday Season.  #FeedingIowans  https://t.co/JUKpwG3yOz

name: Lt. Gov. Adam Gregg
tweet: I visited food pantries in New Virginia, Creston, and Winterset on my #99CountyTour this afternoon to donate food and raise awareness ahead of the holiday season. @FOODBANKIOWA CEO Michelle Book joined me to donate shelf-stable products purchased by the #FeedingIowans Task Force.  https://t.co/DDzWfDsxEj

name: Lt. Gov. Adam Gregg
tweet: Meeting virtually today with a great bipartisan group of lieutenant governors via the @NLGA!  https://t.co/CuEkF06POB

name: Lt. Gov. Adam Gregg
tweet: Students at Orange City Christian School brought in non-perishable food items to school to replenish the depleted shelves of their local food pantry. Great job!  On this #GivingTuesday, I encourage you to follow their lead and donate to your local food pantry.  #FeedingIowans  https://t.co/6GhfyqO3Sf
